When would you want to use a remote repository rather than keeping all your work local?

When colaborating with other people or want to make changes from diferent computers or save the files outside the computer

Why might you want to always pull changes manually rather than having git automatically stay up to date whit remote repository?

Not all the changes want to be pushed all the time

Describe the differences between forks, clones, and branches. When would you use one instead of another?

Forks copy a repository from github to another github account, it is used to modify a personal version of the repository

Clone is used to get a copy of a repository from github to work in your own computer

Branches are used to make experimental changes or make changes that you want to make separetely

What is the benefit of having a copy of the last known state of the remote stored locally?

to keep track of the changes that are being made by other people

How would you collaborate without using Git or GitHub? What would be easier, and what would be harder?

to colaborate without github the code will need to be reviewed often to see the changes everyone made and merge the code manually, with git and github is all advantages and improvements